.TH "usb_intf_get_dma_device" 9 "usb_intf_get_dma_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_intf_get_dma_device \- acquire a reference on the usb interface's DMA endpoint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct device *" usb_intf_get_dma_device
.BI "(struct usb_interface *intf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "intf" 12
the usb interface
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
While a USB device cannot perform DMA operations by itself, many USB
controllers can. A call to \fBusb_intf_get_dma_device\fP returns the DMA endpoint
for the given USB interface, if any. The returned device structure must be
released with \fBput_device\fP.

See also \fBusb_get_dma_device\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
A reference to the usb interface's DMA endpoint; or NULL if none
exists.
